Wayland: fix drag-and-drop aborting the process (glfw/glfw#2835, glfw/glfw#2562)

GLFW 3.4 (release) advertises wl_data_offer at version 3 but its listener
only wires up the `offer` event, leaving the v3 `source_actions` (opcode 1)
and `action` (opcode 2) handlers NULL. Modern compositors emit those events
during a drag, so the instant a file is dragged onto the window
libwayland-client calls

    wl_abort("listener function for opcode 1 of wl_data_offer is NULL")

and the whole process dies with SIGABRT before any drop is delivered. Add
no-op handlers for those events; GLFW only needs the offered mime types to
decide what to accept on drop.

Also guard two NULL dereferences on the same code path (fixed in GLFW
master, changelog "A drag entering a non-GLFW surface could cause a
segfault"): dataDeviceHandleEnter dereferenced `window` for drags over
non-GLFW surfaces, and dataDeviceHandleDrop passed a possibly-NULL dragFocus
to _glfwInputDrop (the guarding assert is compiled out in release builds).

Fixed upstream in GLFW master, but not in the 3.4 release nixpkgs builds.

--- a/src/wl_window.c
+++ b/src/wl_window.c
